<h4> CV </h4>

<h5>Personal details:</h5>

<p>
Name: Gijs Jasper Wijnholds <br />
Date of Birth: 6 May 1990 <br />
Nationality: Dutch <br />
Residence: Utrecht, the Netherlands <br />
Contact: See <a href="contact.html">here</a>
</p>

<h5>Research interests:</h5>

<p>
My main current research interests lie in the application of logic to language. In particular, I am interested in the use of <i>substructural logics</i> to analyse natural language syntax, and putting them to further use in guiding semantic analysis. I have been working on issues of the generative capacity of type logical models, relating substructural logics to formal language theory. More recently, I have worked on the connection between (substructural) logic and category theory and its application in the setting of distributional semantics. <br />

Keywords: type logical grammar, category theory, compositional distributional semantics.
</p>


<h5>Education:</h5>

<ul>
<li>
2011-2014 MSc in Logic at the Institute for Logic, Language and Computation at the University of Amsterdam (<i>cum laude</i>). Graduated on type logical models of grammar in relation to category theory (in particular graphical languages) and distributional semantics.
</li>

<li>
2008-2011 BSc in Artificial Intelligence at Utrecht University (<i>cum laude</i>). Graduated on categorial grammar, in particular the Displacement Calculus and extensions of pregroup grammars.
</li>

</ul>

